name: Digits Sum
description:
Let's define 
    S(x)
 to be the sum of digits of number 
    x
 written in
decimal system. For example, 
    S(5) = 5
, 
    S(10) = 1
, 
    S(322) =
    7
. We will call an integer 
    x
 interesting if 
    S(x + 1) < S(x)
. In
each test you will be given one integer 
    n
. Your task is to calculate the
number of integers 
    x
 such that 
    1 
    ≤ x 
    ≤ n
 and 
    x
 is
interesting. Input The first line contains one integer 
    t
 (
    1 
    ≤ t
    
    ≤ 1000
) — number of test cases. Then 
    t
 lines follow, the

    i
-th line contains one integer 
    n
 (
    1 
    ≤ n 
    ≤ 10^9
) for
the 
    i
-th test case. Output Print 
    t
 integers, the 
    i
-th should
be the answer for the 
    i
-th test case. Example Input 5 1 9 10 34
880055535 Output 0 1 1 3 88005553 Note The first interesting number is equal
to 
    9
.
